<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 08 at 8:37PM EDT until June 08 at 9:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 900 PM EDT
FOR NORTHERN KANAWHA...SOUTHEASTERN ROANE AND WEST CENTRAL CLAY
COUNTIES...
At 837 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Elkview, or 11
miles northeast of Charleston, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Charleston, Sissonville, Clendenin, Pinch, Elkview, Amma and
Procious.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM EDT for central West
Virginia.
For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
